                          Employment Opportunities


   Return to Previous Page

   Employment Opportunities Main Page

   Information Technology Jobs

   Canyon Springs Employment Opportunities

   General Information on State Employment

   State Application

   State Personnel Board



   The Department of Developmental Services employs approximately 9,500
   full- and part-time employees in a variety of positions including
   clinical, trades and clerical positions. The majority of these are in
   the developmental centers. Most positions are covered by the California
   State civil service process and are generally filled through
   competitive examinations. The department also contracts with 21
   regional centers to coordinate the delivery of services for persons
   with developmental disabilities and their families.

